SIMPLE: bravely
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bravely
<hw>Brave"ly</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>In a
brave manner; courageously; gallantly; valiantly; splendidly;
nobly.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Finely; gaudily; gayly; showily.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And [she] decked herself <qex>bravely</qex> to allure the eyes of
all men that should see her.</q> <rj><qau>Judith. x. 4.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Well; thrivingly; prosperously.</def>
<mark>[Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Braveness</ent>⟦br⟧
